  "prompt": "What is colour of water?",
  "response": "Pure water is colorless. In small quantities, it appears clear and transparent. However, when viewed in larger volumes, such as in lakes or oceans, water can appear blue due to the absorption and scattering of light. Other factors like the presence of impurities, algae, or minerals can also affect the coloration of water, leading to various shades including green, brown, or even red in certain conditions.",
